-- Ontario Teachers Appoints Kozun to Replace Mock in Team Shuffle
-- B y   K a t i a   D m i t r i e v a
-- 2013-09-09T19:13:16Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-09-09/ontario-teachers-appoints-kozun-to-replace-mock-in-team-shuffle.html
Ontario Teachers’ Pension Plan ,
 Canada ’s third-largest pension manager, appointed Wayne Kozun
senior vice president of fixed income and alternative
investments, as part of an investing team shuffle.  Kozun, who is senior vice president of public equities,
replaces Ron Mock, who succeeds Jim Leech as chief executive
officer on Jan. 1, the Toronto-based  fund manager  said today in
a statement.  Jane Rowe will keep her title as senior vice president of
Teachers’ private capital unit, and will also be responsible for
the long-term equities group and will replace Mock on the board
of directors of Cadillac Fairview, the fund’s real estate unit.  Other role changes in the investment team include Michael Wissell, senior vice president of tactical asset allocation and
natural resources, who will replace Kozun. Ziad Hindo, currently
a vice president of global opportunities and natural resources,
will replace Wissell.  All the appointments in the division, headed by Neil
Petroff, are effective Oct. 21. Teachers’ manages C$129.5
billion ($124 billion) in assets for 303,000 members in Ontario.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Katia Dmitrieva in Toronto at 
